credible? Rash treaty commitments to the feud-prone <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">nations</ENAMEX> of central <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Europe</ENAMEX>
led to <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT">World War I</ENAMEX>--could it happen again? ("Putting a tripwire for war on
<ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Poland</ENAMEX>'s border," is how <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Buchanan</ENAMEX> put it in a <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Feb. 5</TIMEX> column.) Why can't <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Europe</ENAMEX>,
